<section class="hero-landing" id="highland-hero">
  <div class="page-description">
    <h1 class="pageTitle">Highlands</h1>
    <p>People who settled the mountains and hills. Due to the difficulty of taking the high ground, Spanish conquistadors and missionaries found little success in ruling or influencing highland communities. Highlanders used simple tools; their
      livelihoods mainly depended on hunting and gathering, bolstered by agriculture. Some highland dwellers traded among themselves and lowland dwellers, while some preferred isolation. Under the American and Philippine governments, they were able
      to stay in their homes and keep their culture. However, most highland communities are dying out along with their practices, or are intermingling into the larger Filipino population.</p>
  </div>
</section>



