      <h2>Aeta</h2>
      <p>The Aeta, also known as the Agta or Ati, are aborigines believed to have been one of the first to settle the Philippines over 30,000 years ago. The Spanish called them Negritos because of their dark skin and short stature. They lived
        scattered among the mountains of Luzon and were nomadic. The Aeta organized themselves in decentralized tribes and used iron tools. Some Aeta groups believe in one supreme deity called Apo Na who ruled over lesser spirits while some believe
